ruleArray.label: Liberal Arts and Sciences General Education Requirements

textList: As required by South Carolina statute (Sect. 59-29-120 and Sect. 59-29-130),
all degree-seeking undergraduate students admitted or readmitted Fall 2021
forward must earn 3 credit hours from a list of faculty approved courses
designated to satisfy the Founding Documents requirement as outlined in state law.
Approved Founding Documents courses may also fulfill other degree requirements
(e.g. general education, major, minor, or First Year Experience).  This requirement
must only be satisfied once at the College of Charleston.

textList: Complete one course that satisfies the U.S. component and one
course that satisfies the global component from the list of
approved Race, Equity, and Inclusion (REI) Requirement
(6 credit hours). Approved REI courses may also fulfill other
degree requirements (e.g. general education, major, minor,
First Year Experience, or Founding Documents). The two courses
do not have to be taken from the same department or in sequence.
Students with 45 or more earned transfer credit hours at the time
of admission or readmission, are required to complete only one
REI-designated course, either U.S. or Global.
